trans-unit.target: I'm Nicolas a Software Engineer graduated from the school Epitech, in France. I began learning Computer Science when I was in High School. At the time I was creating small games using python. Then I learned Low-Level languages such as C, C++ or the x86 Assembly. Entering my university allowed me to work as an intern for several company projects while continuing to learn the computer theory. During my 4th year, I went to study in San Diego, California where I've mainly studied computer networks and security. One year after coming back to France, I started my first job working on the Rafale F4 for Dassault Aviation, through the services company Capgemini. I became independent in 2020. Since that time, I'm performing several missions as a freelance. In the end, I've been working on many projects from Low-Level System Applications Development to Website Integration passing through Artificial Intelligence and Systems Security. If you look for a Web Developer or a Mobile Developer, don't hesitate to contact me.
Need to create a software product from scratch or to maintain it ? Take advantage of the services provided by a passionate expert in IT.
Improve the quality of your software applications
Bypass the limitations of embedded systems
Secure your applications from potential attackers
Take benefits of each platform's capacity
Boost your applications by optimizing your data management
Enjoy a very high sound quality track
Obtain the score for your soundtrack
Finding simple and reliable solutions for solving complex problems.
Producing clean and easily understandable code for more efficiency.
Bringing ideas and feedback for improving your project.
After a first contact, let's establish the quote and define the methods and the deadlines for your project.
Once the quote is established, let's agree on the mission and start working on it, together.
Now that everything is set, you can let me create a very high end product made with lots of passion, just for you.

I'm Nicolas a Software Engineer graduated from the school Epitech, in France. I began learning Computer Science when I was in High School. I started my first job working on the Rafale F4 for Dassault Aviation, through the services company Capgemini. I became independent in 2020. Since that time, I'm performing several missions as a freelance. In the end, I've been working on many projects from Low-Level System Applications Development to Website Integration passing through Artificial Intelligence and Systems Security. Here, you will get an overview of my professional experiences and about some of the projects I realized.
First, here's a timeline of my experiences...
First year at Epitech after a Baccalauréat in Sciences. Learning many elementary programming languages such as C and C++, and many programming concepts.
First internship as a Software Engineer at Orchestra Travelsoft. Integrating, optimizing and maintaining platform applications. Security scripts development.
Internship as an Open-Source Developer at Cadageo. Creating Splicy, an extension for the software Qgis which is supposed to help the optical fiber deployment in France. SQL Requests Optimizations.
Study abroad at California State University San Marcos. Studying Game Programming with Unity, data communication and computer networks, real-time concepts for embedded systems, and entrepreneurship.
Teaching assistant for Web@cademie by Epitech. Teaching web technologies to the Web@cademie students. Correcting and grading the students' projects during their presentations.

Internship as a Business Intelligence Engineer. Third Party Maintaining on BI applications for the french health insurances system. Optimizing and fixing the software CAMEL, which secures the communications from the Cnam to the national database (SNIIRAM). Creating a script for automatically updating the mapping of every SNIIRAM application, under Neo4J.
First job as a Software Conceptor at Capgemini. Integrating a geolocation algorithm for the Dassault Rafale F4.
